## Privacy Policy

**Effective date:** March 1, 2026

TapRVU respects your privacy. This policy explains what data TapRVU stores and how it is used.

### 1. Data TapRVU stores

TapRVU may store the following app data you enter:

- Procedure logs and related totals (for example wRVU totals)
- Templates, favorites, and combo configurations
- App preferences (for example goals, reminders, and display settings)
- Optional profile details you provide (for example specialty, role, region, institution)

### 2. No patient identifiers (no PHI)

TapRVU is intended for personal productivity tracking and **does not require patient identifiers**.  
Users should not enter patient names, MRNs, or other protected health information (PHI).

### 3. Where data is stored

By default, data is stored locally on your device.

If you enable account/cloud backup features, backup data may be stored in your own private cloud account space associated with your device/account settings.

Deleting the app will remove locally stored data unless backed up to your personal cloud account.

### 4. Data sharing

TapRVU does not sell your personal data.

TapRVU does not share your personal app content with third parties for advertising.

If optional analytics or feedback features are used, only the limited data required for those features is sent.

### 5. Notifications

If enabled by you, TapRVU can send local reminders (for example, to log activity).  
You can disable notifications in iOS Settings at any time.

### 6. Your controls

You can:

- Edit or delete logs in the app
- Export your data
- Disable reminders and optional features in Settings

### 7. Contact

For questions about this Privacy Policy, contact: taprvu@gmail.com

### 8. Disclaminer 

TapRVU is a productivity tool and does not provide medical advice or billing services.
